From cou.: 15 The extraction method used (Fig. 1) has been described elsewhere.27 It consists in mixing 50 g of a chopped sample with anhydrous sodium sulfate and dichloromethane, the mixture is homogenised and filtered. The solvent is removed under vacuum at 40 °C in a rotary evaporator until almost dry and then to the point of dryness with a slight N2 stream, then re-dissolve with 5 mL of cyclohexane.
From Soup: 15 The extraction method used ( Fig. 1 ) has been described elsewhere. 27 It consists in mixing 50 g of a chopped sample with anhydrous sodium sulfate and dichloromethane , the mixture is homogenised and filtered. The solvent is removed under vacuum at 40 °C in a rotary evaporator until almost dry and then to the point of dryness with a slight N 2 stream, then re-dissolve with 5 mL of cyclohexane .
 ###### 
From cou.: 16 This method was applied to blank samples of each commodity in order to obtain uncontaminated extracts for use in preparing the matrix-matched calibration curves. It was also applied to spiked samples to obtain the recovery rates.
From Soup: 16 This method was applied to blank samples of each commodity in order to obtain uncontaminated extracts for use in preparing the matrix-matched calibration curves. It was also applied to spiked samples to obtain the recovery rates.
